theorem Topology.frontier_frontier_subset_frontier
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (frontier A) ⊆ frontier A := by
  intro x hx
  -- Decompose the membership in the double frontier
  rcases hx with ⟨hx_clF, hx_not_intF⟩
  -- `frontier A ⊆ closure A`
  have hF_subset_closureA : frontier A ⊆ closure A := by
    intro y hy
    exact hy.1
  -- 1. Show `x ∈ closure A`
  have hx_clA : x ∈ closure A :=
    (closure_mono hF_subset_closureA) hx_clF
  -- 2. Show `x ∉ interior A`
  have hx_not_intA : x ∉ interior A := by
    intro hx_intA
    -- Use `mem_closure_iff` with the open set `interior A`
    have h_nonempty :
        ((interior A) ∩ frontier A).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hx_clF (interior A) isOpen_interior hx_intA
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hy_intA, hy_frontierA⟩⟩
    -- From `y ∈ frontier A` we have `y ∉ interior A`, contradiction.
    exact hy_frontierA.2 hy_intA
  -- Assemble the membership in `frontier A`
  exact And.intro hx_clA hx_not_intA
